  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n*Summary*: when user disables access to location and tries to send location in Chat (using /location command), he sees only loading indicator without any descriptive error\r\n![location](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/33398967/32741010-7625d246-c8ad-11e7-9f00-f1892d1012ef.png)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nError or popup kind of \"Enable location in Settings or type address manually\"\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nOnly loading indicator is shown\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Go to Settings > Status\r\n- Allow Status to access Location > set \"Never\" (workflow for IPhone)\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Login with existing user\r\n- Open 1-1 or Group chat\r\n- Tap on /location command\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n*Status version: 0.9.12\r\n*Operating System: iOS 10.3.2\r\n",
